{"id": "1369438107186761729", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "1013180159697891340", "author_name": "roto_rooster", "content": "Ok I think I've cracked the vague code of what N's kit is going to be like and I'm also almost convinced he's gonna be the male ultra they mentioned a long time ago.\n\nFirst - the trio isn't really a trio, it's more like a quartet. We know thais tawil N as the 3 principles/bodies but tulu is an honorary fourth from a game perspective. He's one of the stronger awakers in lore, maybe not as strong as the big 3 and he's handicapped, but definitely one of the stronger characters. He's also a soft mascot for the game since he's the first limited, and the first limited is always usually a pseudo mascot (fgo - saber, genshit - venti, wuwa - jiyan) and the devs definitely have a bias for him seeing as we're getting gtulu and he had buffs not too long ago. The other thing is that the game being lovecraft inspired can always go for the low hanging fruit of ctulhu tentacle stuff but thankfuly it hasn't dipped into just that exclusively. But anyways, the game kind of references this chart that lovecraft made as a half joke which is a kind of family tree (thais is basically tulu's grandma) -> https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1324466276470624279/1352254771351785544/IMG_1223.png?ex=681b4f65&is=6819fde5&hm=f04abdc6afa37bed6647900f1a60987d95fd420aa98deafb636ec915b70e5fd2&", "timestamp": "2025-05-06T22:18:07.683000+00:00", "embeds": [{"type": "image", "title": "", "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1324466276470624279/1352254771351785544/IMG_1223.png?ex=681b4f65&is=6819fde5&hm=f04abdc6afa37bed6647900f1a60987d95fd420aa98deafb636ec915b70e5fd2&", "description": ""}]}
{"id": "1369438115260923905", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "1013180159697891340", "author_name": "roto_rooster", "content": "this goes into the next aspect of the quartet covering the 4 realms, we have tulu for aequor, thais for caro and tawil for chaos, it would be odd to not have ultra and instead double down on another realm, especially since we've been teased about a male ultra for months now. ||This is cute, but there's another tidbit I'm gonna hinge on for this theory that is tied to chapter 8. The orisons representing the big 3 are vaguely based around their kits, and with the exception of tawil's orison for some reason being blue, they most likely match their realms too.||\n\n||Fertility - red for caro, fills your hand with a card (albeit doesn't reduce cost like e2 thais), so like her exalt|| \n\n||Wisdom - draws, deals with costs (potentially tied to tawil being able to ignore arithmetica costs and eat skey instead?), again weird they made it blue and not yellow to represent chaos but they were thinking of eos so they might've been rushed. But it still lines up with tawil's wing forms.|| \n\n||Delight - discards every card except those of the owner and gives you random cards. It's purple like ultra and if we look at the previous two orisons, we can tell that this most likely is a loose representation of N's kit, not sure what part of it but definitely some part of it, it's definitely not unlikely we get a discard (aftershock) focused meta or set of characters now that we got corp, and i've honestly been half thinking doresain might focus on discarding a lot.|| \n\n||But anyways, we can also dig into a lore version of these, with fertility orison duplicating excessively to try and survive the gaze of the supreme will, the wisdom orison... expanding your options? making things not as they seem? (the way tawil was hiding is unconventional but this is a stretch) and we can link the delight orison to N's personality - selfish and single minded, focused on experiences and viewing things as nothing more than shows for him to enjoy||", "timestamp": "2025-05-06T22:18:09.608000+00:00"}
